.TH "rdma_copy_src_l2_addr" 9 "rdma_copy_src_l2_addr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_copy_src_l2_addr \- Copy netdevice source addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rdma_copy_src_l2_addr
.BI "(struct rdma_dev_addr *dev_addr "  ","
.BI "const struct net_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_addr" 12
Destination address pointer where to copy the addresses
.IP "dev" 12
Netdevice whose source addresses to copy
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBrdma_copy_src_l2_addr\fP copies source addresses from the specified netdevice.
This includes unicast address, broadcast address, device type and
interface index.
